    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Tracking TV Preferences</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Cass R Lewart letter on Aug 24 article note TiVo and ReplayTV collect data on programs watched and will sell it to advertisers, raising privacy issues</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>''Don't People Want to Control Their TV's?'' (Aug. 24), about TiVo and ReplayTV, did not address important privacy issues.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>''Don't People Want to Control Their TV's?'' (Aug. 24), about TiVo and ReplayTV, did not address important privacy issues.</p>
        <p>Information about every program request and the programs being watched are collected by TiVo and ReplayTV.</p>
        <p>Selling such information to advertisers will be a main revenue stream for TiVo and ReplayTV.</p>
        <p>As many consumers may object to such uses of information about themselves, that could be the Achilles heel of the new technology.</p>
        <p>CASS R. LEWART  Holmdel, N.J.</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
